JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 159
EP  - 161
VL  - 16
IS  - 1
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - The article presents a reply to comments made by Donald D. Bowen and Robert F. Byrne on the author's article ?Relationships Among Role Accuracy, Compliance, Performance Evaluation, and Satisfaction Within Managerial Dyads,? published in the June 1972 issue. The author asserts that the interpretations by Bowen and Byrne of the study results were in their own self-interest and not in the terms of the content of the article. Furthermore, the author argues Bowen and Byrne's interpretation of the causality of the study, which is said to independent of the original issue.
AB  - The article presents a reply to comments made by Donald D. Bowen and Robert F. Byrne on the author's article ?Relationships Among Role Accuracy, Compliance, Performance Evaluation, and Satisfaction Within Managerial Dyads,? published in the June 1972 issue. The author asserts that the interpretations by Bowen and Byrne of the study results were in their own self-interest and not in the terms of the content of the article. Furthermore, the author argues Bowen and Byrne's interpretation of the causality of the study, which is said to independent of the original issue.
