N2  - The article presents a letter from the editor regarding several changes to the periodical during the transition of the past editor to the present one. Part of the change includes the expansion of the Editorial Review Board, the introduction of a new type face, and the attempt to achieve a greater standardization of headings and references. Also, Robert D. Fulmer has taken over as the periodical's first advertising manager and Mary Green Miner has assumed the duties of the new position of production editor. Furthermore, the editor has no plans for any additional themed issues with solicited articles, because of the amount of manuscripts still awaiting publication.
